Key Match Events: Sacramento Kings closed with a 15-0 run to rally past the Philadelphia 76ers 113-107
Miscellaneous Highlights: Tyrese Maxey made at least three shots from beyond the arc in 10 straight games, a franchise record
Others: De'Aaron Fox scored 35 points, Malik Monk added 20 points and six assists, Domantas Sabonis had 17 points, 21 rebounds and seven assists, Paul George had 30 points, eight rebounds and five assists for the 76ers, Joel Embiid (sprained left foot) and Kelly Oubre Jr. (sprained left hand) did not play for the Sixers, Keegan Murray was sidelined for the Kings with left ankle soreness
